## Basic Calculator (Java)

This project contains a simple Java program that performs a **single arithmetic operation** on two numbers.  
It allows the user to input two numbers and choose an operation (`+`, `-`, `*`, `/`).
## ðŸ“– Description
- Prompts the user to enter **two numbers**.
- Asks for the **desired operation**: `+` (addition), `-` (subtraction), `*` (multiplication), `/` (division).
- Performs the calculation based on the chosen operation.
- Prints the **result** of the calculation.
- Handles **division by zero** and invalid operations gracefully.
ðŸ“Œ Learning Concepts
Taking user input with Scanner
Using if-else statements
Performing arithmetic operations
Handling errors such as division by zero and invalid inputs
